annotationA: 3-hydroxyisobutyryl-CoA hydrolase, mitochondrial; Hydrolyzes 3-hydroxyisobutyryl-CoA (HIBYL-CoA), a saline catabolite; Belongs to the enoyl-CoA hydratase/isomerase family
annotationB: Probable 3-hydroxyisobutyrate dehydrogenase, mitochondrial; NAD binding; phosphogluconate dehydrogenase (decarboxylating) activity; 3-hydroxyisobutyrate dehydrogenase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular amino acid metabolic process; valine metabolic process; pentose-phosphate shunt
